---
const title = "The Segmented Nerd";
---
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<title>{title}</title>
		<style>
			body { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; background: #1a1a1a; color: #e0e0e0; padding: 2rem; line-height: 1.6; }
			h1 { color: #00ff41; border-bottom: 2px solid #333; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; }
			.card { background: #2a2a2a; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 5px solid #00ff41; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
			.hobby-tag { background: #333; padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.8rem; margin-right: 0.5rem; }
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<h1>THE SEGMENTED NERD</h1>
		<p>Staff Technical Account Manager | Woodworker | 3D Printing Enthusiast</p>
		
		<div class="card">
			<h2>Field Note: Why 'Any-Any' is a Liability</h2>
			<p>In VCF 5.x, vDefend isn't just a firewall; it's your ignition lock. If your vCenter can talk to your Guest Wi-Fi, you haven't built a cloud; you've built a liability.</p>
			<a href="#" style="color: #00ff41;">Read More...</a>
		</div>

		<div class="card" style="border-left-color: #ff9f00;">
			<h2>The Shop & Lab</h2>
			<p>Recent Build: 1x4 Lego Display for the boys. Functional Print: F-350 Center Console Bracket (PETG-CF).</p>
			<span class="hobby-tag">Woodworking</span><span class="hobby-tag">3D Printing</span>
		</div>
	</body>
</html>
